name: Building Smart Pipelines with Cloud Build

venue.name: Deloitte
venue.address_1: L17, 80 Queen St, Auckland, 1010, New Zealand

description:
Join us for a talk about Cloud Build, one of the powerful features of Google's Cloud Platform.
With Cloud Build, not only can you automatically build your applications and push the Images into the registry, you can actually design and build up CI/CD pipelines, from basic to really advanced ones.

Meet our speaker: Thomas Laegler
Thomas is a passionate Software Engineer, and an enthusiastic GCP user.
Utilizing many GCP features in multiple projects, he brings a lot of experience. After graduating and working as an IT-Consultant in Hamburg, Thomas came to New Zealand with his Backpack and decided to stay.

We'll meet at 17:30 with drinks and pizza, with the talk beginning at 18:00.
Hope to see you all there!

Thanks Deloitte New Zealand, for hosting the meetup and providing food and drinks !

name: Kubernetes Starter

venue.name: GridAKL
venue.address_1: GridAKL, Lysaght Building, 101 Pakenham Street West

description:
Join us to a light talk about Kubernetes.
We will discuss mostly the WHY, rather than the HOW.
No code, just the theory. Microservices, Containers & Kubernetes.
Beginners are welcome.
18:00 - gathering, pizza & beers
See you.

name: Cloud Dataflow - smart stream and batch data processing
description:
Cloud Dataflow is a fully-managed service for transforming and enriching data in stream (real time) and batch (historical) modes.
With Dataflow, it's easy to setup processing pipelines for integrating, processing and analyzing large data sets.

Our speaker, Steven Wang, is a Cloud Native Architecture advocate.
He is a Specialist Lead in Deloitte, and holds 3 Google Cloud Platform certificates.

We will gather at 17:30, with pizza and beverages. The talk will start at 18:00. See you all !

Thanks Deloitte NZ, Google and GridAKL, for supporting our group.
